The paper deals with fundamental graph problems in the Massively Parallel Computation (MPC) framework, which is related to distributed computing and graph algorithms. The paper specifically focuses on the Maximal Independent Set (MIS) problem on trees with strongly sublinear memory. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Additionally, the paper involves algorithmic techniques and complexity analysis, which are related to cs.AL (Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
